		<div id="comment_body_65423343"><p><div class="quote"><p>So the citizens are freely allowed to leave and visit other countries as they see fit?</p><p>I've never heard anyone refer to North Koreans as savages though, only that they're oppressed and the government does a poor job of making it a good place to live (evidenced by the difficulty in leaving).</p></div><p>Yes, it certainly is difficult to leave North Korea legally.   I seem to recall reading that following a major defector in Europe bailing from a North Korean embassy with his family that now North Korea makes people who leave the country leave their families behind in North Korea.   But I do want to point out something that you and maybe most Slashdotters don't understand at all.   <br> <br>

Most people don't want to leave their country no matter how bad it gets.   <br> <br>

Communist governments generally don't understa<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

